                                    <style>
                                      <CSS value="text-align:left;vertical-align:top;width:50%;padding-right:20px"/>
                                    </style>
                                  </tableCell>
                                  <tableCell>
                                    <contents>
                                      <textItem>
                                        <dataSource>
                                          <staticValue>What if these users could set "yesterday" in a global parameter and Cognos Analytics would always remember this setting? What if they could set "last Sunday", which is another common use case? Or what if they just want to use the _as_of_date and be able to set any date they choose? Well now they can with the Time Perspective global parameter. This new ability to set a dynamic date solves this problem and saves time/effort for end users.</staticValue>
                                        </dataSource>
                                      </textItem>
                                    </contents>
                                    <style>
